channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.description: Republicans warn that California's SB 898, designed to improve protections against sexual abuse in prisons, might reduce sentences for violent offenders.

item.title: Trump Campaign Hits Harris for What She Didn't Say
item.description: Donald Trump's presidential campaign slammed Kamala Harris for all of the issues she didn't address during her first interview since announcing she was running to be the Democrat nominee 40 days ago.

item.title: WATCH: Kamala Harris Gives Disqualifying Answer When Asked About Defense of 'Biden's Capacity to Serve'
GOP senators look to tie crackdown on noncitizen voting to must-pass spending bill
item.description: Some GOP lawmakers want to see a GOP priority Trump-backed bill tied to a spending measure next month as Congress contends with another potential government shutdown.

item.title: Trump Promises Revival of American Dream
item.description: In a town hall event in Wisconsin, former President Donald Trump vowed to restore the American dream, focusing on economic revival, energy independence, and reducing living costs.

item.title: Kamala Harris on CNN: Officially Flips on Fracking, Then Flops When Asked to Defend Her Shift in Position

item.description: The Trump-Vance campaign released a statement Thursday night following Vice President Kamala Harris' interview with CNN, calling her a 'San Francisco radical.'

item.title: Gabbard Discusses Fertility Struggles as Trump Promises Free IVF
item.description: Former Rep. Tulsi Gabbard detailed her struggles with infertility during a town hall with former President Donald Trump that streamed live on Newsmax2 on Thursday.

item.title: Second Gentleman Doug Emhoff Tries—and Spectacularly Fails—to Get Dem Crowd to Chant 'USA'

item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris offered a vague day one plan should she take the Oval Office next her in her first sit-down interview since becoming the Democratic nominee.

item.title: Trump at Wisconsin Town Hall: Walz 'Is a Weird Dude'
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz, Democrat Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate, hasn't been shy in calling their Republican rivals, former President Donald Trump and Ohio Sen. J.D. Vance, weird.
